Verma said , “ China is involved in destroying the Indian economy and is posing danger to the country while the Chief Minister wants to bring Chinese industries in the state which will pose a threat to our markets .” “ The CM should have instead made efforts to provide roads and basic facilities in the state ,” he said , questioning Chauhan whether he had taken the permission of the BJP ’ s national leaders for the trip and informed the Union Home Minister on Chinese investment in the state .